##The father and son, the conductor and the nurse, rushed to the front line of the fight against the plague

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Editor's Note: This is a father and son. Father Zhao Huaming is the train captain of the beijing-shanghai railway section. Seventeen years ago, during the SARS period, he ran 1461 / 1462 beijing-shanghai green leather cars. This year, when the COVID-19 epidemic, he still out, running passengers, go to Chongqing. Unlike 17 years ago, Zhao Cheng, the son of a primary school student, is now a nurse at the North Hospital of Shanghai Ruijin Hospital, and is currently participating in the rescue of patients with severe cases of new coronavirus pneumonia in Guanggu district of Wuhan Third People's Hospital. When Darling was less than six months old, his new father and grandfather went to the front..

Dictation | Zhao Huaming, Zhao Cheng

Organized by Jiang Haofeng

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cheng Zhao and his colleagues in Wuhan | CCTV screenshot

Zhao huaming: Go out to ride, do not hesitate to rent a house and small sun is separated

As a staff member of Shanghai Passenger Transport Section, I have been working in the beijing-shanghai motorcade for a long time. In 2003, during SARS, I went to Beijing. Back then, 1461 / 1462 was a green car with no air conditioning. I was on the front line, I faced the epidemic, I was not the conductor at that time, and I never flinched. Now as a train captain, in the face of the epidemic, it should take the lead to do a good example, do a good job in the train epidemic prevention and control work, to ensure the safety and comfort of passengers travel. It's my biggest responsibility. I am confident that with our efforts, we will be able to overcome the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
2003 SARS period, Shanghai Railway passenger section staff to do a good job before the ride protection work, photography | Zhang Jinwei

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Huaming, the conductor of this year's Spring Festival travel rush, asked the train to do a good job of protection

Looking back on this year before the Spring Festival, when I was traveling from Shanghai to Chengdu, I felt that there might be a major epidemic. At that time, the motorcade had already taken it seriously, and the cadres of the motorcade were sent back and forth to take more rides. In addition, N95 masks and protective clothing were issued in case of emergency. And a thermometer.

When I tested a patient with a fever. The man got on the bus from Hangzhou, and when I detected that he had a fever, I immediately quarantined him. He then contacted the Xinyu Railway Station duty officer and handed the passenger over to Xinyu Railway Station. The train went on, and in the middle of the night, I read on my phone that there was a new case of pneumonia in Xinyu. That was a shock. Imagine a 14 day quarantine for 40 people on the entire train, our entire train attendant, the conductor, the conductor, the guard, and even the interns. During the SARS period, some of our colleagues who ran Beijing cars were quarantined. There is a female intern in our class. She has the same name as my son, also called Zhao Cheng. She is a student of Changzhou Railway. Put yourself in her shoes. If something happened, wouldn't her parents be in a hurry? I immediately called Xinyu Railway Station to confirm that the new patient was not the one I had brought to the station. That was a relief.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao huaming takes temperature of passengers

In the early morning of New Year's Eve, Linke arrived at Chengdu station. About 3:15, I got a call from home. My Wife told me that my son was about to leave for Wuhan. My son is a 25-year-old nurse at Ruijin North Hospital. His daughter-in-law is a colleague and a nurse. The family has just had a little grandson, less than half a year old.

To be honest, I'm in a bit of a hurry. At home is this situation, and what the epidemic situation, I was outside the sports car and experienced SARS, roughly know some. But in my mind, I still support my son's retrograde trip to Wuhan. On the one hand, I knew that he had been working as a nurse in the intensive-care unit for two years after graduation, and that this was the time for a young man like him to be in the front line. On the other hand, I felt that the protective equipment of the hospital was always better than that of our railway units, as long as you follow the rules and regulations, you should be able to guarantee safety.

After his son stayed at home for several days, he left for Wuhan on the third day of the New Year. After that, I video-linked with him every day. For example, today he works from 0:00 to 4:00, so I talk to him after work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao huaming signs up with an APP for travelers to Shanghai

In the unit, I am an old employee, and is an active member of the party, more experienced SARS, I took the initiative to the team, please give me an assignment. After the festival, I went out again. This visit is from Chongqing to Shanghai. Due to the outbreak, there aren't many tourists. We strictly enforce the rules and regulations, for each passenger to do a good job of temperature, APP registration information and other work. This time I will follow the car to Xuzhou after Chongqing. In order to ensure the safety of my family, especially the safety of my grandson, I rented a room ready to self-isolation. The House is online to find, from his home near the subway a station road distance, intermediary fee 600 yuan, rent 2000 yuan per month, are paid online, suddenly borrowed half a year. Because of the reason of on-line intermediary, I did not meet with intermediary, landlord. The landlord, who is from Nanping, Fujian Province, is not in Shanghai and says he will not return to Shanghai for a while. I think it's kind of like fate. I was a soldier in Nanping in 1991, preparing to go to the front if something happened in the Taiwan Strait. Now in a situation, I think, should be rushed to the front line or to go forward..

Zhao Cheng: new severe coronary pneumonia patients need more psychological care

My wife was with me when I got the call from the hospital for advice. She is also our Ruijin Hospital North Hospital nurses, we are husband and wife, but also colleagues. In a word, what was it like? She knew.

My mother also supports me to go to Wuhan to support, just hope I take care of myself outside. It's a baby. My baby's barely six months old. My Dad's a conductor. My Mom's not retired. Fortunately, my wife's family is also very supportive of me going to Wuhan, so I can rely on them to take care of Darling. The hospital is very concerned about my family. My wife works the day shift now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Cheng poses for a photo before wearing a protective suit

I left on January 28th. Guanggu district of Wuhan Third People's Hospital, originally a General Hospital, has been transformed into an infectious disease hospital. We have four nurses, two men and two women, and colleagues from other hospitals working in the North Hospital of Ruijin Hospital. Compared to the first batch of colleagues in Wuhan at that time, our current shift schedule is to work 4 hours, rest 16 hours. The previous batch had started working long hours, even in diapers. Our current scheduling, but also a comprehensive consideration of the manpower, as well as wearing isolation suits can not eat, toilet and other circumstances.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Cheng (right) and his colleagues, photographed by the doctor's mobile phone on duty, all wrote their names on the protective clothing because they had difficulty recognizing each other in wearing the protective clothing

On our day off, we stayed in a hotel near the hospital, two to a room. The hotel is about 20 minutes'walk from the hospital, but we usually take the shuttle bus. 24-hour service in hotel restaurants. We also eat in restaurants sometimes. Because the restaurant strict disinfection, coupled with a small staff, do not have to worry about infection in the restaurant. In addition, some outside businesses know that we are the Hubei medical team, to deliver food to us.

Tell me about the job. After I graduated from school, I worked at the intensive-care unit, where I encountered a lot of critically ill patients. Most of them are in critical condition. Many are in Comas. Most of the severe cases of new coronavirus pneumonia encountered in Wuhan were not like this. They're much more sober. From the nursing point of view, I feel that the new coronavirus pneumonia patients need more psychological care. They have trouble breathing, anxiety. We should pay special attention to these aspects and sum up the nursing experience.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhao Cheng, a nurse in Guanggu district of Wuhan Third People's Hospital

17 years ago, the SARS epidemic. At that time, I was still in the second grade of Nanxiang Primary School. What I remember now is taking my temperature at the school gate. My Dad used to drive a Beijing car. The experience of SARS has now been put to use. All in all, I hope we can work together to win this must-win battle against the plague.

The images in the article are provided by the interviewee in addition to the byline
